&lt;p&gt;Who we are&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Arcadia is the AI-powered energy intelligence platform for businesses. We replace fragmented tools and manual workflows with one platform to pay utility bills, buy energy, and advance sustainability — across every location, at enterprise scale. Trusted by Fortune 2000 companies, Arcadia combines unified data, AI-powered analytics, and expert advisory to help enterprise teams save money, mitigate risk, and cut carbon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We deliver this through three comprehensive solutions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Utility Bill Management: Automating the entire utility bill lifecycle — from data capture and validation to payment processing and auditing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Energy Procurement Advisory: Bringing together comprehensive data, AI-powered analytics, market expertise, and a strong partner network to make sophisticated procurement options accessible to all. .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Sustainability Reporting — Verified emissions data with seamless integration into leading sustainability platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tackling the world&#39;s most complex energy challenges requires diverse thinking. We&#39;re building teams of people from different backgrounds, industries, and disciplines — united by a belief that energy management should be simple, intelligent, and a genuine driver of business value.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job summary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Security Engineer, you’ll be the technical anchor of Arcadia’s security operations function, leading the daily defense of our endpoints, cloud infrastructure, and identity systems. You’ll operate with significant autonomy and strong collaboration across our global team, drive initiatives end to end, and partner directly with security leadership in the U.S. to mature our detection, response, and vulnerability management programs. You’ll also support our SOC 2 Type II program by owning the technical controls within your scope.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person will report to the Senior Manager of Security in the U.S., with strong local collaboration in Chennai, India. You’ll work as part of a single global security team operating with consistent expectations and shared standards across the globe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a Senior Security Engineer based in Chennai, India with 5 to 8 years of experience in security operations, endpoint security, and cloud security. This is an Individual Contributor role at the Senior (L4) level, anchored in SecOps with expected contributions to security engineering work. The ideal candidate is technically deep, operationally disciplined, and comfortable driving programs end to end with light oversight. You should be equally at ease tuning an EDR detection, leading a vulnerability remediation effort with key stakeholders, and leading security incident response. You’ll bring strong judgment, clear written communication, and the ability to translate technical risk into business terms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role goes beyond reactive security analyst work and includes leadership of detection, response, and engineering initiatives. You’ll be expected to shape how Arcadia’s security operations function evolves, mentor teammates, and contribute to the broader security strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Arcadia, we value demonstrated experience over certifications. Whatever certifications you hold or don’t hold, what matters most is the depth of your hands-on security work and the impact you’ve had on the teams and programs you’ve supported.&lt;/p&gt;
